Package: whSample
Type: Package
Title: Utilities for Sampling
Version: 0.9.6.2
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
Authors@R: person("Paul", "West", role=c("aut", "cre"),
        email="fp8049@gmail.com")
Description: Interactive tools for generating random samples. Users
        select an .xlsx, .csv, or delimited .txt file with population
        data and are walked through selecting the sample type (Simple
        Random Sample or Stratified), the number of backups desired,
        and a "stratify_on" value (if desired). The sample size is
        determined using a normal approximation to the hypergeometric
        distribution based on Nicholson (1956)
        <doi:10.1214/aoms/1177728270>. An .xlsx file is created with
        the sample and key metadata for reference. It is menu-driven
        and lets users pick an output directory. See vignettes for a
        detailed walk-through.
